text.__SUMMARY__:
Baeckea exserta is a shrub found in central Western Australia.The low shrub typically grows to a height of 0.4 metres (1.3 ft). It blooms between August and November producing pink and white flowers.
It is found on sand-plains and scrubland in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia between Tammin and Kellernerrin where it grows in sandy soils.
